# Installation Guide For Project Elixir on Begonia/Begoniain

### CLEAN FLASH (RECOMMENDED)
0. Flash from latest MIUI 12.5.7.0 MI recommended
1. Wipe - Advanced Wipe - System, Vendor, Cache, Dalvik/ART cache - Wipe it
2. Installation - Flash ROM (don't flash gapps!)
3. Installation - Flash DFE (optional, but twrp can't decrypt data) (<a href=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jdngb4JUReLQUJf6MqMtVsx52y5qeK-d/view>link here</a>
4. Wipe - Format data - Write "yes" - Format it
5. Reboot and enjoy
6. (Optional) - Flash latest Magisk v25.x archive (after first boot) (<a href=https://github.com/topjohnwu/Magisk/releases>link here</a>)

### DIRTY FLASH IF AN UPDATE
## SOME UPDATES REQUIRE CLEAN FLASH (Check notes on update post)
1. Wipe - Advanced Wipe - System, Vendor, Cache, Dalvik/ART cache - Wipe it
2. Installation - Flash ROM (don't flash gapps!)
3. Installation - Flash DFE (ONLY IF FLASHED ON CLEAN FLASH) (<a href=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jdngb4JUReLQUJf6MqMtVsx52y5qeK-d/view>link here</a>
4. Wipe - Advanced Wipe - Cache, Dalvik/ART cache - Wipe it
5. Reboot and enojoy
6. (Optional) - Flash latest Magisk v25.x archive (after first boot) (<a href=https://github.com/topjohnwu/Magisk/releases>link here</a>)

## Note
1. Recommended to update all Google packages after first setup
2. Some updates require clean flash. If there isn't a note on the update post or on xda then you can dirty flash.
3. Clean flash is always recommended
